= Marinaleda is a town and municipio of the province of Seville, Andalusia, Spain. The town is a Libertarian Communist farming cooperative, of 2,700 people.[4] In 2008 its population was 2,708 people. Its surface is 25 km², with a density of 109.11hab/km².

